  "text": "To generate a plasmid to restore the functional ospA allele, we inserted a gentamicin resistance marker in the ospB gene of pOKLP54, leaving ospA intact. pOKLP54 was digested with PvuII and BclI to remove 567 bp of ospB. The resistance cassette vector pTAGmA, containing the aminoglycoside acetyltransferase (aacC1) gene of Tn1696 linked to the flaB promoter of B. burgdorferi [CITATION_1] , was digested with PvuII and BamHI. The pOKLP54 backbone fragment and the flaB p -aacC1 cassette were isolated by agarose gel electrophoresis with BlueView stain (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO), purified with QIAquick, and ligated. Transformants of E. coli TOP10 selected on 50 g/ml kanamycin-5 g/ml gentamicin LB plates were screened for the expected construct by PCR and restriction digest to yield pOKOSPA-CЈ.",
